President Trump delivered remarks at the G20 Summit in Hamburg, Germany, announcing a new initiative to empower women entrepreneurs. He praised Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau and German Chancellor Angela Merkel for their leadership, and thanked his daughter Ivanka for her advocacy on behalf of women entrepreneurs. The initiative aims to provide access to capital and mentors for women running their own businesses, with the goal of promoting economic growth and lifting people out of poverty. The United States will contribute $50 million to the initiative. President Trump described the initiative as a historic effort that will transform millions of lives.